		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">This is a collaborative project between Oxford, Warwick, Southampton and Sussex Universities, and is devoted to a study of the formation of periodically domain inverted non-linear optical crystals.  These materials show immense promise for efficient frequency doubling of low power laser sources and will be applied to a wide variety of devices in bulk or waveguide form.  The basic physics of the domain inversion process will be studied using x-ray anomalous scattering, structural studies and optical experiment.  It is intended to establish which crystals are susceptible to domain inversion, particularly using electron beam direct write techniques.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
